data.value: The Negovan eco path, also known as Emen's eco path, is the first eco path in Bulgaria. It is in close proximity to the Emen canyon. It marks the beginning of an eco path that begins with a cave and ends with the fairytale Momin Jump on the Negovanka River, which forms a whirlpool where you can take a bath or indulge in fishing. It is possible mainly to catch the chub. The walk takes about 3 hours. The hills have a view of the river, and around the trail there are plenty of lawns to relax.
